reviews.review_text: Not great recording from FM First set is very poor quality for a soundboard.  It is listed as being taped from the FM source, but by what, I don't know.  A Fischer-Price tape recorder?  Remember those ones you'd put by the radio and press Play and Record together?  The second set is redeemed though with a much better recording.  Also, Truckin' is cut off a few seconds.  There is another source that has Truckin' complete, with introduction.  3 Stars for poor "SBD" source first set.  Typical '71 show.  No Wharf Rat again...

Good Set While somewhat muted on the highs, overall i think this is a pretty good show given that it was recorded in '71.  Show seems upbeat with nice piano from Keith and especially like the cryptical suite.  previous review was a bit one sided and perhaps overly critical of sound, yet this is clearly not an audience tape.  the source states it was recorded off FM so if you don't like it, find another show.
